ps Munis BPATVA etc These are two of the key differences between the gas industry and the electric industry  Pipelines were separated from LDCs and producers and there is no native load exception to inter-state pipeline access I think the reliability arguments some may bring up agianst these two fundamental changes are contestable and winnable  This should take away the FERC fear of jeopardizing reliability 
